# Files matched by these patterns ARE copied into new Claude Code
# desktop auto-worktrees (under .claude/worktrees/<session-name>/),
# despite being gitignored. Patterns use .gitignore syntax.
#
# Why this matters: .claude/settings.json carries the project's hook
# wiring (qa_scenario_guard, docs_guard, zombie_check) and a
# machine-specific home path. Without this file, every "+ New session"
# would land in a worktree with no hooks active.

.claude/settings.json
.claude/settings.local.json
